> If you're craving something that's good and hearty, this recipe has got you covered. Beef tenderloin is rubbed with cinnamon and smoked paprika, which brings a layer of warm aromatics to the meat. It's then roasted and drizzled in a cherry jam sauce that adds sweetness to all that savory. The mashed potatoes on the side stay creamy and classic, but there are also tender roasted carrots with a sprinkle of chili flakes for a pop of heat.

Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Dice @potatoes{12%oz} into 1⁄2-inch pieces; place in a #large pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

Meanwhile, toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread across entire sheet.)

Roast on middle rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Rub with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @cinnamon{1%tsp}. Rub 13⁄4 tsp spice mixture (3 1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings) over pork. (Reserve remaining spice mixture for the next step.)

Once carrots have roasted 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully place pork on empty side. (For 4, add pork to a second sheet and roast on top rack.)

Roast until pork is cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes} more. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

While pork roasts, add @cherry jam{2} and @white wine vinegar{1%tsp} (1 1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings) to #bowl{} with reserved spice mixture; stir to combine. (Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!) Microwave until warm, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Mash drained potatoes with @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice pork crosswise.

Toss carrots with a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste.

Divide pork, mashed potatoes, and carrots between plates. Drizzle sauce over pork and serve.

> Once carrots have roasted 5 minutes, swap in chicken for pork. Roast until chicken is cooked through, 15-18 minutes more.

> Once carrots have roasted 8 minutes, swap in beef for pork. Roast until beef is cooked to desired doneness, 12-15 minutes more.

> Slice chicken crosswise or slice beef against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.